'''''Halsbury's Laws of Australia''''' is similar to ''[[Halsbury's Laws of England]]'', but is written for [[Australia]]. It is an [[encyclopaedia]] of the [[Australian law|laws of Australia]]. Published by [[LexisNexis]], it is one of the two foremost legal encyclopaedias in Australia, the other being ''[[The Laws of Australia - Encyclopedia]]'' by Lawbook Co.<ref name=UAdel>{{cite web | title = Legal Encyclopedias | publisher = The University of Adelaide Library | accessdate = 2012-08-24| url = http://www.law.adelaide.edu.au/library/research/encyclopaedias/}}</ref>

''Halsbury's Laws of Australia'', like other legal encyclopaedias, provide a summary on the current state of laws of Australia. Subjects are arranged systematically by subject area and covering all nine jurisdictions, with case and statute law authorities which support legal propositions.<ref name=UAdel /> 

