The '''Ice Age Centre''' is a museum dedicated to the understanding of [[ice age]]s, located in [[Äksi]] village, [[Estonia]].
The museum strives to popularise knowledge about the origins and dynamics of different ice ages, including their effect on the landscape, animal life and humans, with a special focus on the impact of the latest ice age on what is today Estonia.<ref name="centre">{{cite web |url= http://www.jaaaeg.ee/about-iceage-center|title= About Ice Age Centre|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date= |website= |publisher= Ice Age Centre|accessdate=2 September 2013}}</ref>
This museum offers a variety of educational history as well as an overview of the future for families to come in and learn more about. The Ice Age Centre was named the Best Tourist Venue of 2012 <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jaaaeg.ee/en/about-ice-age-centre/|title=About Ice Age Centre - the Ice Age Centre|website=jaaaeg.ee|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-04-19}}</ref>. Each floor within the building offers different exhibits. The 1st floor contains the exhibits ''ICE AGE AND ICE IN OUR ERA''. The 2nd floor contains the exhibits ''TRACES OF ICE AGE ON THE ESTONIAN TERRITORY.'' The 3rd floor contains the exhibits ''DOES THE FUTURE DEPEND ON US?''<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://jaaaeg.ee/en/about-ice-age-centre/|title=About Ice Age Centre - the Ice Age Centre|website=jaaaeg.ee|language=en-GB|access-date=2018-04-19}}</ref>
