{{Infobox Court Case | name = J v Director General, Department of Home Affairs | court = [[Constitutional Court of South Africa]] | image = | imagesize = | imagelink = | imagealt = | caption = | full name = J and B v Director-General, Department of Home Affairs and Others | date decided = 28 March 2003 | citations = {{cite SAFLII |court=ZACC |year=2003 |num=3 |parallelcite=2003 (5) BCLR 463, 2003 (5) SA 621 (CC)}} | transcripts = | judges = [[Arthur Chaskalson|Chaskalson]] [[Chief Justice of South Africa|CJ]], [[Pius Langa|Langa]] [[Deputy Chief Justice of South Africa|DCJ]], [[Lourens Ackermann|Ackermann]], [[Richard Goldstone|Goldstone]], [[Tholie Madala|Madala]], [[Yvonne Mokgoro|Mokgoro]], [[Dikgang Moseneke|Moseneke]], [[Kate O'Regan|O'Regan]] & [[Zak Yacoob|Yacoob]] JJ | number of judges = 9 | decision by = Justice Goldstone | prior actions = | appealed from = [[Durban and Coast Local Division]] | appealed to = | subsequent actions = | related actions = | opinions = | keywords = | italic title = force }} '''''J and B v Director-General, [[Department of Home Affairs (South Africa)|Department of Home Affairs]] and Others''''' is a 2003 decision of the [[Constitutional Court of South Africa]] which dealt with the situation of children born via [[artificial insemination]] to a lesbian couple in a permanent life-partnership. The court ruled that the partner who was not the biological parent was to be regarded as a natural parent and guardian and that the children were [[Legitimacy (family law)|legitimate]] in law, and ordered the [[Department of Home Affairs (South Africa)|Department of Home Affairs]] to register both partners as parents on the children's birth certificates.<ref>{{cite news |first=Phillip |last=de Bruin |title=Lesbians: Biological parents |newspaper=News24 |date=11 February 2003 |url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Lesbians-Biological-parents-20030211 |accessdate=20 July 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Lesbians' twins 'legitimate' |newspaper=News24 |date=28 March 2003 |url=http://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/Lesbians-twins-legitimate-20030328 |accessdate=20 July 2011}}</ref>
